artoo.js

//////////////////////////installing artoo.js///////////////////////////

go to medialib.github.io/artoo/quick_start/

open GoogleChrome and click on view and select "Always show bookmark bar"

drag the artoo logo which is under the header installation into your bookmark bar.If successfull it will say "artoo" in your bookmark bar. 

you will know that you were successfull if you open your javascript browswer console (command, option, 'j') and click on the bookmark icon you will see this,"

artoo-latest.min.js:2    .-""-.   
  /[] _ _\  
 _|_o_LII|_ 
/ | ==== | \
|_| ==== |_|
 ||LI  o ||
 ||'----'||    artoo.js
/__|    |__\   v0.3.2
artoo-latest.min.js:2 [artoo]: info - jQuery was correctly injected into your page (v2.1.3).
artoo-latest.min.js:2 [artoo]: info - artoo is now good to go! "

You are read to go. 
First test go to hackernews.com, click on the artoo bookmark and copy and paste this code into your console.

artoo.scrape('td.title:nth-child(3)', {
  title: {sel: 'a'},
  url: {sel: 'a', attr: 'href'}
}, artoo.savePrettyJson);

you should get a data.json file that has all the titles and links from the front page of the site.

wanna try a more complex scraper? paste this inside your console.

artoo.scrape('tr tr:has(td.title:has(a)):not(:last)', {
  title: {sel: '.title a'},
  url: {sel: '.title a', attr: 'href'},
  domain: {
    sel: '.comhead',
    method: function($) {
      return $(this).text().trim().replace(/[\(\)]/g, '');
    }
  },
  score: {
    sel: '+ tr [id^=score]',
    method: function($) {
      return +$(this).text().replace(/ points/, '');
    }
  },
  user: {
    sel: '+ tr a[href^=user]',
    method: function($) {
      return $(this).length ? $(this).text() : null;
    }
  },
  nb_comments: {
    sel: '+ tr a[href^=item]',
    method: function($) {
      var nb = +$(this).text().replace(/ comments/, '');
      return isNaN(nb) ? 0 : nb;
    }
  }
}, artoo.savePrettyJson);

/////////////////////////tools/commands/////////////////////

artoo.scrape - scrape data 
artoo.save - download the scraped data 
artoo.ajaxspider - crawls and triggers a series of ajax requests that passes the accumulated data to a final callback.
artoo.ajaxSniffer - helps you grab some of the circulating data of the web page you need to scrape.
	artoo.ajaxSnigger.before - Gives you a chance to register a callback to be fired any time an ajax request is made by the page.

	artoo.ajaxSnigger.after - Gives you a chance to register a callback to be fired any time an ajax request is completed by the page.

	artoo.ajaxSnigger.off - Remove the given callback from the ajax sniffing stack.

////////////////////////////examples//////////////////////////

// Get any quoted text from a page and save it to a json file
var quotes = [];
artoo.scrape('p', {
text: function($) {
var text = $(this).text();
var quote = text.match(/"(.*?)"/);
if (quote != null) {
quotes.push(quote[1]);
}
}
}, function() {
artoo.savePrettyJson(quotes);
});

// Get the content, href, and class of all anchor tags on a page
artoo.scrape('a.links_wrapper__link', {
content: 'text', 
href: 'href', 
class: 'class'
});

